    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>Ael</abbr><ex>ius</ex></expan> Verissimus <lb n="2"/>pr<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>e</abbr><ex>fectus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>co</abbr><ex>llegii</ex></expan> q<expan><ex>uin</ex><abbr>q</abbr><ex>uennale</ex></expan> sc<expan><ex>h</ex><abbr>o</abbr></expan><lb break="no" n="3"/>l<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>e</abbr></expan> Vari<supplied reason="lost">a</supplied>no in <lb n="4"/>honorem col<lb break="no" n="5"/><supplied reason="lost">l</supplied>egi posuit <lb n="6"/>Arriano <lb n="7"/>et Papo co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ulibus</ex></expan> <lb n="8"/>VIII <expan><abbr>Kal</abbr><ex>endas</ex></expan> Ianua<lb break="no" n="9"/>rias
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Alföldy zufolge handelt es sich bei Aelius Verissimus um einen praefectus eines collegiums, dessen (magister) quinquennalis zur Zeit der Aufstellung ein Varianus war. Reste von roter Farbe in den Buchstaben. Z. 1: AE-, VE-, MV-Ligatur; Z. 3: VA-Ligatur; Z. 8: AN-Ligatur. (B): CIL 03, 04496: Z. 1: CL Verissimus; Kremer: Z. 1: [A]el(ius); CIL 03, 04496; Vorbeck: Z. 2: RE COOQ; CIL 03, 04496; Kremer: Z. 3: [l](a)e; CIL 03, 04496: Z. 3: VARNIO.</p>
            </div>
